PSTAT W 174 HW5

data <- read.csv('train.csv')
# just get date and sales data for store 1 and item 1
item1sales <- subset(data, store == 1 & item == 1, select = c(date, sales))
item1sales
data

2. Plot

t = 1:length(item1sales$sales)
plot(t, item1sales$sales, xlab='Date', type='l', ylab='Sales for Item 1', main="Time Series Plot of Item 1 Sales")

3. Differencing to attain stationarity

diff1 <- diff(item1sales$sales, lag=365)
t1 <- 1:length(diff1)
plot(t1, diff1, type='l')

diff2 <- diff(diff1, lag=7)
t2 <- 1:length(diff2)
plot(t2, diff2, type='l')

4. ACF and PACF

acf(diff2, lag.max=400)

pacf(diff2, lag.max=300)
